	<h3>SUN FLOWER</h3>
	<img src="images/sun flower.jpeg" alt="Sun flower" width="200" /><br>
	
	<p>DETAILS
	
Scientific Name: Helianthus annuus.

Appearance: Sunflowers are known for their large, bright yellow blooms that resemble the sun. They can grow up to 4 meters tall and have a unique trait called heliotropism, where young flowers turn to face the sun.

Origin: Native to North America, sunflowers have been cultivated for centuries and are now grown worldwide.

Uses: The seeds, petals, and even the leaves of sunflowers are utilized in various ways, from food to industrial applications.

BENEFITS

Nutritional Value: Sunflower seeds are rich in healthy fats, proteins, vitamins (like E and B-complex), and minerals such as magnesium and selenium.

Heart Health: The seeds contain unsaturated fats that help reduce bad cholesterol levels, promoting cardiovascular health.

Skin Care: Sunflower oil is widely used in cosmetics for its moisturizing and anti-inflammatory properties.

Environmental Benefits: Sunflowers are used in phytoremediation to clean contaminated soil by absorbing toxins like lead and radioactive substances.

Stress Relief: The vibrant appearance of sunflowers can uplift moods and reduce stress.
